SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT This SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) dated as of July 11, 2019 (the “Effective Date”), is made and entered into by and between Golden west power partners, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Owner”), and GRAZING YAK SOLAR, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Licensee”). Owner and Licensee may each be referred to herein individually as a “Party”, and collectively as the “Parties”. RECITALS WHEREAS, Owner owns and operates an approximately 249.4 MW wind-powered electric generating facility located in El Paso County, Colorado, known as the Golden West Wind Farm, as further shown in Exhibit B attached hereto (the “Owner’s Project”); WHEREAS, Licensee will construct, own and operate a 36 MWac solar facility located in El Paso County, Colorado near the city of Calhan, known as Grazing Yak Solar, with a commercial operation date scheduled for December 31, 2019, as further shown in Exhibit B attached hereto (the “Licensee’s Project”). The Owner’s Project and the Licensee’s Project may each be referred to herein individually as a “Project,” and collectively as the “Projects”; WHEREAS, Owner has entered into a Large Generator Interconnection Agreement (“Owner GIA”) with Public Service Company of Colorado (“Transmission Provider”) dated January 12, 2012, as amended August 5, 2014, and Licensee has entered into a Large Generator Interconnection Agreement (“Licensee GIA,” jointly with Owner GIA, the “GIAs” or “Interconnection Agreements”) with Transmission Provider dated January 31, 2019, as amended May 22, 2019. WHEREAS, Owner owns the Shared Facilities (as defined in Exhibit A), which facilities are critical to the operation of Owner’s Project and Licensee’s Project. NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows: AGREEMENT TERM; EARLY TERMINATION Term. The term of this Agreement shall commence on the date first written above and shall continue in effect until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties, or (b) pursuant to Section 1.2 of this Agreement. Early Termination. This Agreement shall automatically terminate, without further action by any Party and without further liability of any Party to any other Party, upon the date that both Parties, or their successors and assigns, shall have permanently ceased operation of the Projects for the production of electric energy. If only Owner ceases operations of its Project, the Parties shall act in good faith to amend and restate this Agreement to continue this Agreement on terms substantively similar to this Agreement. GRANT OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS AND SHARING OF INTERCONNECTION SERVICE Grant. Owner hereby grants to Licensee, during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary in connection with the ownership, operation and maintenance of Licensee’s Project. Essential Nature. Owner hereby acknowledges that the right of Licensee to access and utilize the Shared Facilities is essential to the production of electric energy by Licensee’s Project, and to the delivery of such energy to the transmission system. Vesting. The right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities granted hereunder by Owner to Licensee shall vest in Licensee, as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title, leasehold or other interest or rights in the Shared Facilities. NATURE OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS Limitation on Grant. Subject to Section 3.3 hereof, the grant of rights under this Agreement by Owner to Licensee is made only to the extent that such rights do not limit in any material respect the ability of Owner to comply with the terms and conditions of the Owner GIA. For the avoidance of doubt, the grant of rights under this Agreement by Owner to Licensee shall not relieve Owner of its obligations under the Owner GIA. Assignment or Transfer of Rights. Except as set forth in Section 9.6 hereof, Licensee shall not assign or transfer any rights granted to it hereunder with regard to the Shared Facilities, or grant any permission, license, right of way or similar right with regard to the Shared Facilities, without the prior written consent of Owner. Interference. Subject to the terms of this Agreement, in no event shall any Party be entitled to exercise its rights to access and utilize the Shared Facilities if the exercise of such rights would materially interfere with, or limit the reasonable and necessary access and utilization of, the Shared Facilities by any other Party or inhibit (a) Licensee’s ability to comply with the terms of the Licensee GIA or (b) Owner’s ability to comply with the terms of the Owner GIA. Prior Written Consent. Except as set forth in this Agreement, Owner shall not take any action that results in the forbearance, foreclosure, termination or alteration of the respective rights or increases the obligations or responsibilities of Licensee of access to, utilization of or reliance upon the Shared Facilities, as applicable, without the prior written consent of Licensee. MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES Allocation of Certain Costs and Expenses. Subject to Section 4.1(ii) and Section 6.4 hereof, Owner shall be responsible for the ownership or possession, operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities. Owner has engaged or will engage NextEra Energy Operating Services, LLC (the “Operator”') pursuant to an operation and maintenance agreement entered into or to be entered into by and between Owner and Operator (the “O&M Agreement”) to perform the Services (as defined therein) for the Shared Facilities. Subject to Section 6.4 hereof, Licensee agrees that all Reimbursable Costs (as defined in the O&M Agreement), the Operating Fee (as defined in the O&M Agreement), and all other costs, expenses, penalties, and liabilities of any kind with respect to the Shared Facilities (regardless of whether or not any such costs, expenses, penalties, or liabilities are incurred in connection with the O&M Agreement, are payable to the Operator or a third party, or otherwise) (collectively, “Shared Facilities Costs”) of Owner, including, without limitation, real property taxes, shall be allocated in accordance with their respective pro rata share, which as of any date of determination, shall be equal to a fraction, the numerator of which shall be the installed capacity in respect of a Project, and the denominator of which shall be the aggregate installed capacity in respect of both Projects (the “Pro Rata Share”); provided that Owner’s payments for any costs, fees, expenses, penalties, or liabilities that are classified in this Agreement as Shared Facilities Costs shall not increase beyond what they were before this Agreement took effect, and that any such increased costs, fees, expenses, penalties, or liabilities shall be paid solely by Licensee, and provided further that if any new Shared Facilities are required solely for service to Licensee (“Incremental Shared Facilities”), then Licensee shall pay all the costs of such Incremental Shared Facilities, including increased operating and maintenance costs attributable to such Incremental Shared Facilities. Licensee shall make its respective portion of any payment due and payable by it hereunder to Owner with respect to any Shared Facilities Costs, in a time and manner that will allow Owner to comply with its payment obligations under the O&M Agreement or otherwise. Owner shall submit monthly invoices in amounts to Licensee for such costs and expenses, and Licensee shall pay Owner on or before the 5th calendar day of the month following receipt of such invoice or, if such day is not a business day, on the next succeeding business day. Any payment for retail station power service shall be the responsibility of Owner and Licensee, respectively. Solely in connection with the Services performed on the Shared Facilities, Owner agrees to pursue all available remedies against the Operator available to it under the O&M Agreement as may be commercially reasonable. Subject to Section 6.4 hereof, the receipt of any payments for liability incurred by the Operator under the O&M Agreement with respect to the Services performed on the Shared Facilities shall be allocated based on the Pro Rata Share and Owner shall make a payment to Licensee for such allocations as soon as reasonably practical following receipt of such liability payments from the Operator. 4.2 Successor Agreement. In the event that the Projects and the Shared Facilities are no longer operated and maintained by a single entity for any reason, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate mutually agreeable terms and execute a mutually agreeable agreement (or amendment to this Agreement) that specifies the division of responsibilities of the entities providing operation and maintenance services associated with the Shared Facilities. CHANGE IN LAW Change in Law. In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Shared Facilities, any of the Projects, or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal, state or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement. If, despite the use of good faith efforts, the Parties are unable to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms, Owner shall be deemed to have authorization to determine on behalf of the Parties such amendment, modification or replacement as is appropriate and consistent with prudent industry standards, the Owner GIA, the Licensee GIA, and Applicable Law, and the other Party shall enter into any amendment, modification or replacement proposed by Owner. CERTAIN COVENANTS Authority and Operational Abilities. Each of the Parties represents, as of the Effective Date, and covenants for the term of this Agreement, that such Party has the legal authority and operational abilities to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement. Payment of Certain Studies, Upgrades and Facilities. In the event that Owner at any time shall have paid, funded or posted as security pursuant to the Owner GIA any amounts required under such agreement for facility upgrades or studies to the extent arising as a result of the interconnection of Licensee’s Project and required under the Licensee GIA, Licensee shall promptly, on demand, either post alternative security, or pay or reimburse the amounts paid or funded to Owner. Observance of the Interconnection Agreements. Owner shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement and the Owner GIA in a manner that is reasonable and not discriminatory against Licensee. Licensee shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement and the Licensee GIA in a manner that is reasonable and not discriminatory against Owner. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement: Owner and Licensee each agree to operate its respective Project in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the Owner GIA and Licensee GIA, respectively, and in a manner consistent with the terms of such agreement. Owner and Licensee each agree to assume and be bound by all obligations related to its respective rights to receive interconnection service, directly or indirectly, as set forth in the Owner GIA and Licensee GIA, respectively. Owner and Licensee each agree to use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with the operation of its respective Project that might reasonably be expected to result in a default under the Owner GIA and Licensee GIA, respectively, and if such default occurs, to promptly cure such default in accordance with the terms of the applicable agreement. Owner and Licensee each agree to provide each other with all reasonable information regarding the operation and condition of its respective Project required for each other to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the Owner GIA and Licensee GIA, respectively. Each Party agree to provide to each other copies of all material notices and instructions it receives under the Owner GIA and Licensee GIA, respectively, if such notices are reasonably likely to be relevant to the other Party’s rights under this Agreement. Adverse Events and Decommissioning. If an operational issue arises at one of the Projects that could be reasonably expected to result in a material breach by Owner of the Owner GIA, by Licensee of the Licensee GIA or by any Party under this Agreement (an “Adverse Event”), Owner shall curtail the Project that is causing the Adverse Event, or if Licensee’s Project is causing the Adverse Event, Licensee shall curtail its Project. In the event of such curtailment, the Project that has caused the Adverse Event shall not be permitted to deliver energy to the Shared Facilities until such time as the Adverse Event has been cured to the reasonable satisfaction of Owner. If, as a direct result of an Adverse Event, Owner incurs any Shared Facilities Costs, the Project that has caused such Adverse Event shall be solely responsible for reimbursing Owner for any such Shared Facilities Costs. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for Owner, as determined in its sole and absolute discretion, to accurately allocate such responsibility, each Project responsible for the Adverse Event will be liable for its respective Pro Rata Share of such Shared Facilities Costs (provided that, for this purpose, the denominator used in determining the Pro Rata Share shall be the aggregate capacity of the Projects responsible for the Adverse Event only). At the end of the later of (a) the useful life of the Shared Facilities, and (b) a time at which the Shared Facilities are no longer required by any of the Projects (the “Termination of Transmission Activities”), the Project Owners shall, jointly and severally, within twelve (12) months of the Termination of Transmission Activities (the “Restoration Window”) take any and all actions required by any Law (as defined in the O&M Agreement), Government Agency (as defined in the O&M Agreement), or any reasonable requirement by any leasehold or easement grantor to remediate, mothball, decommission, take down, dismantle, and remove all Shared Facilities, and related access roads, and fill up all holes caused by such removal and restore the surface of the real estate underneath the Shared Facilities (the “Shared Facilities Area”) to the same condition as the Shared Facilities Area was prior to entry thereon and use thereof by the Project Owners. Without limiting Section 9.7 hereof, in the event that either Project Owner is required to pay to any party any cost, expense, or liability, which cost, expense, or liability is allocable to another Project Owner pursuant to this Section 6.4, such responsible Project Owner(s) shall indemnify, defend and hold such paying Project Owner harmless from any and all such costs, expenses, or liabilities, including, without limitation, attorney fees. Curtailment. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, in the event of curtailment pursuant to the Interconnection Agreements, or pursuant to applicable operating guides or applicable reliability standards and requirements, or as required pursuant to the Transmission Provider’s market rules and administration by the Transmission Provider of those rules, including with respect to curtailment and dispatch priority, the Parties agree that Owner’s Project and Licensee’s Project shall be curtailed as follows: first, and if necessary in full, the Project (if any) the operation of which is causing the need for curtailment; and thereafter, both Projects, at the same time and to an extent for each Project equal to such Project’s pro rata portion (based on such Project’s nameplate capacity) of the energy delivered to the Point of Interconnection (as such term is defined in the applicable Interconnection Agreement) as of the time immediately prior to the event giving rise to the curtailment. Agreement to Cooperate. Each Party agrees to reasonably cooperate with the other Party so that, subject to the terms of this Agreement, each Project benefits from the full utilization and enjoyment of the Shared Facilities as is necessary for the efficient operation of each such Project. No Liens. Each Party agrees not to grant any mortgages, liens, pledges, charges or security interests (collectively, “Liens”) on the Shared Facilities and to keep the Shared Facilities free and clear of all Liens by such Party other than: Liens for taxes which are either not yet delinquent or are subject to a good faith contest in which adequate reserves are established in accordance with GAAP with respect to the contested item (if and to the extent GAAP requires the establishment of such reserves); defects, restrictions, irregularities, encumbrances (other than for borrowed money) and clouds on title and statutory liens that do not materially impair the value or use of the Shared Facilities for the Projects; pledges to secure statutory obligations relating to worker's compensation and/or unemployment insurance or other social security legislation; carriers', warehousemen's, mechanics', workmen's, materialmen's, suppliers', construction or other similar Liens arising in the ordinary course of business of the Parties or incident to the construction, operation, repair, restoration or improvement of the Shared Facilities for obligations (A) which are not yet due or (B) which are the subject of a good faith contest in which adequate reserves are established in accordance with GAAP (if and to the extent GAAP requires the establishment of such reserves); and Liens arising out of judgments or awards in an amount less than $1,000,000 so long as (i) enforcement of any such Lien has been stayed and an appeal or proceeding for review is being prosecuted in good faith, and (ii) adequate reserves have been established in connection therewith in accordance with GAAP (if and to the extent GAAP requires the establishment of such reserves). MATERIAL BREACH Material Breach by any Party. In the event of any material breach of this Agreement by any Party and such Party's failure to cure such breach within a reasonable time not to exceed thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice from any other Party describing such breach, such Party shall have the right, but not the obligation, in addition to all remedies available to it at law or in equity, to cure the breach on behalf of the breaching Party, or (ii), in the case of a breach by Licensee, suspend the breaching Party's access to all or any portion of the Shared Facilities owned by such non-breaching Party for so long as such default shall be continuing and remain uncured; provided, however, that in the event of any breach by a Party of this Agreement that may give rise to a breach by any other Party pursuant to the terms of its respective Interconnection Agreement, such Party shall not be required to provide the breaching Party hereunder with notice and/or an opportunity to cure in order to exercise the remedy specified in clause (i) or (ii) of this sentence only; and provided, further, that the remedy specified in clause (i) may be exercised, without prejudice to any right or remedy of any Party hereunder, by any lender or investor of such Party. If a Party (or any lender/investor thereof) chooses to cure a breaching Party's default, the breaching Party shall reimburse such Party (or such Party's lender/investor) upon demand for all commercially reasonable costs incurred by such Party (or such Party's lender/investor) in curing such breach. FORCE MAJEURE 8.1 Force Majeure. In the event of an act of God, government order or restraint, war (declared or undeclared) or warlike conditions, act of terrorism, blockade, revolution, strike, lockout, civil commotion, fire, flood, storm, epidemic or any other occurrence beyond a Party's reasonable control (each a “Force Majeure Event”), such Party shall promptly notify the other Party thereof and, so long as such condition shall persist, such Party shall not be liable for the delay in performance of, or the failure to perform, its obligations (other than obligations for payment of amounts due hereunder) under this Agreement caused directly or indirectly thereby. The claiming Party shall give the other Party notice describing the particulars of the Force Majeure Event. Within fifteen (15) days after giving notice of the Force Majeure Event, the claiming Party shall give the other Party an estimate of the Force Majeure Event's expected duration and probable impact. The claiming Party shall continue to furnish the other Party with timely regular reports during the continuation of the Force Majeure Event. Each Party shall immediately exercise commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit the impact to its obligations hereunder as a result of the Force Majeure Event. MISCELLANEOUS Relationship of Parties. The Parties do not intend to create any joint venture, partnership, association or any other entity for the conduct of any business. Nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize any Party to act on behalf of any other Party, except as specifically stated herein. Non-Interference. Subject to Section 3.3 hereof, each Party agrees not to interfere with the reasonable and necessary utilization of the Shared Facilities by any other Party as permitted hereunder. 9.3 Modification and Amendment. The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by all of the Parties, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld. 9.4 Waiver. The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of such Party's right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect. 9.5 Enforceability. Any provision of this Agreement which is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of such remaining provisions hereof. 9.6 Assignment. Neither Party may assign any of its benefits, rights or obligations hereunder to any third party without the prior written consent of the other Party, provided, however, that either Party may collaterally assign this Agreement to any entity, or such entity's agent, in connection with a financing or a refinancing of its respective Project. 9.7 Indemnification. Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold the other Party, its officers, directors, shareholders, members and affiliates, harmless from any and all damages, losses, claims, including claims and actions relating to injury to or death to any person or damage to property, demand, suits, recoveries, costs and expenses, court costs, attorney fees, and all other obligations by or to third parties, arising out of or resulting from the indemnifying Party's performance or nonperformance of its obligations under this Agreement, except in cases of gross negligence or intentional wrongdoing, by the indemnified party. However, in no event shall any Party be liable under any provision of this Agreement for any losses, damages, costs or expenses for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages, including but not limited to loss of profit or revenue, loss of the use of equipment, cost of capital, cost of temporary equipment or services, whether based in whole or in part in contract, in tort, including negligence, strict liability, or any other theory of liability; provided, however, that damages for which a Party may be liable to any other Party under another agreement will not be considered to be special, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages hereunder. Choice of Law, Jurisdiction and Waiver of Jury Trial. This Agreement and the rights and obligations of the Parties hereunder will be governed pursuant to, and enforced, construed and interpreted in accordance with, the laws of the State of New York without regard to principles of conflicts of laws (other than Section 5-1401 of the General Obligations Law of the State of New York). Venue for resolution of any disputes under this Agreement shall be New York County, New York. Each of the Parties irrevocably and unconditionally submits to the exclusive jurisdiction of the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York for the purposes of any suit, action or other proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement, the transactions contemplated hereby, any provision hereof or the breach, performance, enforcement or validity or invalidity of this Agreement or any provision hereof (and agrees not to commence any suit, action or proceeding relating thereto except in such courts). THE PARTIES HERETO EACH HEREBY KNOWINGLY, VOLUNTARILY AND INTENTIONALLY WAIVE THE RIGHT EACH MAY HAVE TO A TRIAL BY JURY WITH RESPECT TO ANY PROCEEDINGS BASED HEREON, OR ARISING OUT OF, UNDER OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT, OR ANY COURSE OF CONDUCT, COURSE OF DEALING, STATEMENTS (WHETHER ORAL OR WRITTEN) OR ACTIONS OF ANY PARTY TO THIS AGREEMENT. THIS PROVISION IS A MATERIAL INDUCEMENT FOR THE PARTIES TO ENTER INTO THIS AGREEMENT. Inspection of Records. Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Shared Facilities held by any other Party upon reasonable notice and at reasonable times. Entire Agreement. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof. Section Headings. The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof. Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument. Several Liability. For the avoidance of doubt, the liability of each of Owner and Licensee is several and not joint and each of Owner and Licensee shall be liable only for its obligations (and not the obligations of the other Project Owner) under this Agreement. Specific Performance. The Parties hereto may demand specific performance of this Agreement. Each Party hereby irrevocably waives any defense based on the adequacy of a remedy at law and any other defense which might be asserted to bar the remedy of specific performance.
